&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthuastic person to join our phlebotomy team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to work across all ouh sites. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must have at least 2 years experience within a GP/Hospital setting.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be flexible and have good skills dealing with patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We work on wards and in opd so you will not be working in one area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It would be helpful if you have experience but we will train you to the&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;required standard.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be able to work mornings/afternoons and will include weekends as required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It would be helpful if you hold a drivers license as you will need to cover all trust sites.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date; Monday 10th November2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
